    fullContent: `<h2>About 2048</h2> <p>2048 is a captivating puzzle game that challenges your strategic thinking and planning skills. The goal is simple yet addictive:combine numbered tiles on a 4x4 grid to reach the elusive 2048 tile. With its elegant simplicity and deep strategic gameplay,2048 has become one of the most popular puzzle games,offering endless hours of brain-teasing fun.</p> <h3>Gameplay Mechanics</h3> <p>The game is played on a 4x4 grid filled with numbered tiles. You can move all tiles in four directions:up,down,left,or right. When two tiles with the same number touch,they merge into one tile with double the value. After each move,a new tile (either 2 or 4) appears in a random empty space. The challenge is to keep combining tiles strategically to create higher numbers while managing the limited space on the board.</p> <p>Every move requires careful consideration. You must think several moves ahead,considering where new tiles will appear and how to position existing tiles for optimal combinations. The game ends when the board is full and no more moves are possible,making space management crucial to success.</p> <h3>Strategic Thinking</h3> <p>Success in 2048 requires a combination of strategy and foresight. The most effective approach is to keep your highest-value tiles in one corner,typically the bottom-right or top-left. This creates a "snake" pattern where you can build up numbers systematically without blocking your path.</p> <p>Another key strategy is to avoid random moves. Each swipe should have a purpose,whether it's creating space,combining tiles,or positioning numbers for future merges. Planning your moves in advance helps prevent the board from filling up prematurely.</p> <h3>Key Features</h3> <p>2048 features clean,minimalist graphics that keep the focus on gameplay. The smooth animations and satisfying tile merging effects make each move feel rewarding. The game tracks your score,which increases with each tile merge,encouraging you to beat your personal best.</p> <p>The game offers unlimited replayability. Each game is different due to the random placement of new tiles,ensuring that no two games are exactly alike. This randomness adds an element of challenge and keeps the game fresh even after hundreds of plays.</p> <p>With its simple rules but deep strategic gameplay,2048 is accessible to players of all ages while offering enough depth to challenge even the most strategic minds.</p> <h3>Tips for Success</h3> <p>Keep your highest tile in a corner and build your numbers in a consistent direction. This prevents your high-value tiles from getting trapped in the middle of the board.</p> <p>Don't swipe randomly. Always have a plan for your next few moves,considering where new tiles might appear.</p> <p>Focus on creating space. Sometimes it's better to make a move that doesn't immediately combine tiles if it opens up more strategic options.</p> <p>Practice patience. Rushing moves often leads to poor positioning and a full board. Take your time to think through each move carefully.</p>`,
