    fullContent: `<h2>About Pacman</h2> <p>Pacman is the legendary arcade classic that has entertained generations of players since its release. This timeless maze-chase game combines simple controls with strategic depth,creating an experience that's both accessible and endlessly challenging. Navigate through mazes,collect dots,and outsmart the colorful ghosts in this iconic game that defined the arcade era.</p> <h3>Gameplay Mechanics</h3> <p>You control Pacman,a yellow circular character,as you navigate through maze-like levels filled with dots. Your primary goal is to eat all the dots in the maze while avoiding the four ghosts that patrol the corridors. The controls are simple:use arrow keys or directional controls to move Pacman through the maze.</p> <p>Each level presents a new challenge as you must clear all dots while the ghosts become increasingly aggressive. The maze layout changes between levels,keeping the gameplay fresh and requiring you to adapt your strategy. Time is always a factor,as you race to clear the maze before the ghosts catch you.</p> <h3>Power Pellets and Strategy</h3> <p>Scattered throughout each maze are four large power pellets. When Pacman eats a power pellet,the ghosts turn blue and become vulnerable. During this time,you can eat the ghosts for bonus points. This mechanic creates exciting risk-reward moments where you must decide when to use the power pellets strategically.</p> <p>The power pellets are your key to high scores. Eating all four ghosts after consuming a power pellet awards significant points,with each subsequent ghost in the same power pellet period worth more points. Timing your power pellet usage is crucial for maximizing your score.</p> <h3>Ghost Behavior</h3> <p>Each of the four ghosts has unique behavior patterns. Blinky (red) is aggressive and chases you directly. Pinky (pink) tries to ambush you by predicting your path. Inky (cyan) uses a more complex strategy,and Clyde (orange) alternates between chasing and retreating. Understanding these patterns is key to survival.</p> <p>As you progress through levels,the ghosts become faster and more aggressive,increasing the challenge. The game requires both quick reflexes and strategic planning to navigate safely through the maze while collecting all dots.</p> <h3>Key Features</h3> <p>Pacman features the classic arcade gameplay that made it a cultural phenomenon. The simple yet engaging mechanics make it easy to pick up,while the increasing difficulty and strategic depth keep players coming back for more.</p> <p>The game includes multiple levels,each with a unique maze layout. As you advance,the mazes become more complex,and the ghosts become faster,creating a progressive difficulty curve that challenges players to improve their skills.</p> <p>With its iconic characters,memorable sound effects,and timeless gameplay,Pacman remains one of the most beloved arcade games,offering fun for players of all ages.</p> <h3>Tips for Success</h3> <p>Learn the maze layouts. Familiarity with each level's design helps you plan efficient routes and avoid getting cornered by ghosts.</p> <p>Use power pellets strategically. Don't waste them when ghosts are far away. Wait for the right moment when multiple ghosts are nearby to maximize your score.</p> <p>Watch ghost patterns. Understanding how each ghost behaves helps you predict their movements and avoid them more effectively.</p> <p>Don't panic. When ghosts are close,stay calm and look for escape routes. Rushing often leads to mistakes.</p>`,
